> Top News Historic 1956 Ferrari race car could bring $28M at auction This undated photo provided by RM Sotheby's in New York shows a 1956 Ferrari 290 MM by Scaglietti, built for Formula One legend Juan Manuel Fangio, that is going on the auction block in New York City where it could sell for more than $28 million. RM Sotheby’s says the Ferrari, chassis 0626, will be offered on Dec. 10, 2015, as part of its “Driven by Disruption” sale. (Tim Scott Fluid Images/Sotheby's via AP) 
